---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Baijiu Glossary: Essential Terms for Beginners';
const description = 'A beginner glossary for baijiu terms including qu, aroma type, sauce aroma, strong aroma, light aroma, and Maotai.';
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
  <header class="article-header"><div class="narrow"><p class="eyebrow">Reference</p><h1>Baijiu Glossary</h1><p class="lede">A plain-English reference for the terms that appear again and again in baijiu buying, tasting, and production.</p></div></header>
  <section class="content"><article>
    <h2 id="qu">Qu</h2><p>A fermentation starter made with grains and microbes. Qu is one reason baijiu develops such distinctive aromas.</p>
    <h2 id="aroma-type">Aroma Type</h2><p>The main style classification for baijiu. It is more useful than judging bottles by color. <a href="/db/">Browse all 6 aroma types with their varieties in the database.</a></p>
    <h2 id="sauce-aroma">Sauce Aroma</h2><p>A savory, complex aroma style made famous by Maotai. <a href="/db/aroma/sauce/">View all sauce-aroma varieties &rarr;</a></p>
    <h2 id="strong-aroma">Strong Aroma</h2><p>A rich, often fruity and cellar-influenced style common across many Chinese banquet bottles. <a href="/db/aroma/strong/">View all strong-aroma varieties &rarr;</a></p>
    <h2 id="light-aroma">Light Aroma</h2><p>A cleaner, grain-forward style that can be easier to understand for some first-time drinkers. <a href="/db/aroma/light/">View all light-aroma varieties &rarr;</a></p>
    <h2 id="gbt">GB/T Standard</h2><p>Chinese national standard codes that classify baijiu production methods and quality grades. Each aroma type maps to specific GB/T numbers (e.g., GB/T 10781.1 for strong aroma). Every entry in the <a href="/db/">baijiu database</a> includes its verified GB/T standard.</p>
    <h2 id="development-bottle">Development Bottle</h2><p>A bottle connected to a major brand group or authorized producer but not necessarily equivalent to the core flagship product. These require careful reading before purchase.</p>
    <h2 id="flagship-bottle">Flagship Bottle</h2><p>The core product line most people mean when they refer to a famous brand. Related products, commemorative editions, and group-affiliated bottles may not carry the same status or resale logic.</p>
    <h2 id="importer-label">Importer Label</h2><p>A market-specific label that can show who brought the bottle into a country legally. It is useful for overseas buyers, but it does not replace careful product identification.</p>
    <h2 id="toasting">Toasting</h2><p>The social act of drinking together, often during meals or banquets. Toasting culture matters, but responsible pacing matters more than blind imitation.</p>
    <div class="next-links">
      <a href="/baijiu-basics/">Start with the basics</a>
      <a href="/how-to-buy-baijiu-outside-china/">Use these terms while buying overseas</a>
      <a href="/types-of-baijiu/">Browse baijiu by aroma type</a>
    </div>
  </article></section>
</BaseLayout>
